FBIS4-56369 "drlat085_j_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-085 Daily Report 2 May 1994 Panama Man Arrested for Pulling Gun Near Perez Balladares Man Arrested for Pulling Gun Near Perez Balladares PA0305011394 Panama City Telemetro Television Network in Spanish 2300 GMT 2 May 94 PA0305011394 Panama City Telemetro Television Network Spanish BFN [From the "Telemetro Reports" newscast] [Text] [Announcer] The authorities have arrested an armed man who was near Ernesto Perez Balladares, presidential candidate for the Democratic Revolutionary Party [PRD]. The man claimed that he was going to be robbed. Here is a report: [Reporter] As Perez Balladares was walking down from stage No. 1 on Balboa Avenue, his security forces subdued a man who pulled a gun. Electoral officials were called and, following consultations, the Police arrested the unidentified man. [Begin PRD leader Francisco Sanchez recording] A man who was standing about 2 meters from our candidate, Dr. Ernesto Perez Balladares, pulled out a gun. Thank God our security forces did a good job and arrested him. We will file charges. The electoral delegates took this man to their headquarters to investigate the incident. We regret this incident and urge all citizens and our opponents to avoid actions of this sort, because they will bring no good to Panama. [end recording]
